Drop -fdeclone-ctor-dtor from -Os

GCC -Os codegen emits a call-site reference for a std::basic_string ctor
that no callee under any configuration emits. Reproduction:

    #include <string>
    #include <vector>
    struct S { std::string a; };
    void f(std::vector<S>& v, S&& s) { v.push_back(std::move(s)); }
    int main() {}

Then in GCC 16 (standard build, any host):

    $ gcc -Os example.cc

Error: undefined reference to std::__cxx11::basic_string<…>::basic_string(…)

--- a/gcc/c-family/c-opts.cc
+++ b/gcc/c-family/c-opts.cc
@@ -1098,5 +1098,5 @@
   /* Declone C++ 'structors if -Os.  */
   if (flag_declone_ctor_dtor == -1)
-    flag_declone_ctor_dtor = optimize_size;
+    flag_declone_ctor_dtor = 0;
 
   if (flag_abi_compat_version == 1)
